T*
() Tj
T*
(The heuristic model is transparent and easy to convert into policy. Only exact time-to-) Tj
T*
(click reuse uses percentile calibration because it is a global duplicate-count signal) Tj
T*
(whose suspiciousness depends on the dataset's observed timer granularity and reuse) Tj
T*
(distribution; the absolute floor protects against weak duplicate counts in smaller or) Tj
T*
(smoother datasets. Other heuristic cutoffs remain fixed or total-rate based because they) Tj
T*
(represent separate behavioral concepts. The confirmed query repetition rule reuses the) Tj
T*
(repeated query/domain and repeated query thresholds and adds weight only when both fire) Tj
T*
(on the same event. The dense burst repetition rule reuses those existing component) Tj
T*
(thresholds and adds weight only when all three are present together, which targets many) Tj
T*
(clicks from the same device cluster in the same second with repeated query patterns. The) Tj
T*
(time-to-click timing bands are intentionally tiered: clicks from 0 to 250 ms are treated) Tj
T*
(as implausibly fast direct evidence, clicks from 20 to 60 seconds add low-weight support) Tj
T*
(for delayed or mechanical click patterns, and clicks above 120 seconds remain a separate) Tj
T*
(extreme timing signal. The regular inter-arrival rule is intentionally narrow because) Tj
T*
(the dataset has no explicit user or session identifier: it only compares clicks with the) Tj
T*
(same region, browser, OS, query, and clicked domain, requires at least eight events, and) Tj
T*
(adds low-weight supporting evidence rather than a standalone bot decision. Structured) Tj
T*
(rule contributions include threshold_mode, with fixed rules reported as absolute and) Tj
